##One bed is hard to find in Wuhan Designated Hospital, and patients are isolated with wardrobe at home

Wechat, boyangcongpeople

The function introduces, peels off the human shell, records the real sensible life. Presented by the in-depth Reporting Department of the Beijing News.

Ma Meilian saw that there were two more patients lying on the floor and all the beds in the exam room were filled with patients. In the end, the husband didn't make it to the exam room.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At noon on January 30, doctors at Tongji Hospital stuck needles into a long line of patients, and the line stretched all the way to the door of the fever clinic.

By Wang Feixiang, Beijing News

Editor | Li Ming, proofread | Lucie, Xingfa

This article is about 4,008 words long and takes about 8 minutes to read

Without a bed, Tao Hanxin, a suspected case of the infection, had to sleep for four days in the aisle of the Emergency Department of Tongji Hospital, receiving oxygen treatment. This aisle, there are seven fold-up bed, "are waiting for the bed of the case. "

Outside the hospital, Lin Mei's family suspected infection after home isolation, because there is no isolation conditions, within half a month 3 family members have been infected with symptoms.

Wuhan has implemented a grading system since January 24 to tackle the problems of long waiting times at fever clinics and delays in the allocation of beds. The patients were screened and classified in the Community Medical Center, and could not be identified as suspected to be transferred to the designated place for isolation and observation.

However, the status quo is that designated hospitals are "hard to find a bed" , and community hospitals are also facing limited capacity, manpower constraints and other problems.

As at 2400 hours on 31 January, a cumulative total of 3,215 cases had been reported in Wuhan. According to the Wuhan Health Commission, 14 third-batch hospitals have been put into use since January 27, which will ease the admission of fever patients to a certain extent. After the completion and use of the two hospitals, the city can provide more than 12,000 beds, or can improve the current situation.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On January 29, Lin Mei (not her real name) delivered medicine to her husband, who had a double lung infection.

A family of three have been infected, isolated in the home wardrobe

At noon on January 28th, she brought Abidor, a pair of blue tablets of hydrochloric acid with a spray of clear plague, to her husband's bedside. Two minutes later, she walked in again, this time to deliver medicine to her mother in the other bed. After these, she began to remind her daughter Li Qing to take her medicine.

The order in which the drugs are delivered is also the order of the degree of illness of the family members. Ten days ago, the mother was diagnosed with "a few infectious lesions in both lungs" ; four days ago, the daughter with "infectious lesions in the left lower lung" ; and three days ago, the husband with "infectious lesions in both lungs" . Less than half a month, a family of four three infected.

According to circular No. 7, for patients who do not need to go to the fever clinic, home observation will be carried out by the communities, and the communities will be responsible for providing good home observation services. Because the symptom is lighter, the doctor once repeatedly exhorts Lin Mei's mother and her daughter, to do well the isolation measure at home.

"But there are no conditions at home, " said Lin.

The house is only 61 square meters in size. Lin Mei had to sleep on a wooden sofa in the living room. The husband and mother had to share a bedroom, "segregated" by a wardrobe. The daughter was in her room, trying not to go into the living room.

On January 23, the first day of the city's closure, "everyone in the family was coughing except for their mother, " the daughter recalled. But compared with the new pneumonia "fever, dry cough, breathing difficulties, " and other symptoms, "there is always one or two do not match, also did not dare to think that way. " They watched television, cooking, as usual, stay at home all day.

On January 26, my father had a fever of 38.2 C and was sore all over. Daughter Li Qing also began to have similar symptoms, by Wuhan Puren Hospital diagnosis, left lower lung infection lesions. The family then realized, "this is no ordinary cold and fever. ".

My father had a CT scan of his lungs at the Ninth Hospital. The doctor told him that he had to be hospitalized as soon as possible and that he might succumb to respiratory failure.

Lin Mei began to fear, the next day at noon, she went to the supermarket to buy two bags of disposable paper bowls, "separate utensils, use and throw away. ".

"The most urgent thing is my husband. My daughter is still young, she should be able to hold on. " She burst into tears. Li Qing hurriedly pulls her hand, "Mo rub the eye, Mo rub the eye, go to wash the hand first. "

According to circular No. 7, pneumonia patients with confirmed or highly suspected COVID-19 infection are under the responsibility of the City Health Commission and arranged to be transported to designated treatment sites for treatment.

Father's condition is urgent, the doctor suggested to be hospitalized immediately, but has not been able to find a bed, in desperation, Li Qingfa micro-blog for help. On January 28, after staff at the Qingshan District Health Institute discovered the contents of the microblog, they arranged for nurses from Wuhan No. 9 Hospital to come to his house to give him injections and medicines, but no hospital was able to provide a bed for him.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On Jan. 26, Tao was admitted to a designated hospital, but he slept in the hospital hallway for three or four days without a bed.

Hospital beds are in emergency. Patients are being treated with oxygen in the corridor

Local media reports on Jan. 29 cited data confirming the shortage of hospital beds in Wuhan. Wuhan's first two batches of designated hospitals (10) provide more than 4,000 beds, "now basically saturated" .

On January 22, Tao Hanxin, a 57-year-old Wuhan resident, had his first fever. They waited until 11 p.m. that morning to see the doctor, Ma Meilian, his wife, recalled. After more than four hours of waiting for the CT and blood test results, "the doctor said it was just a normal fever, prescribed drugs, let's go home to continue to observe. "

On January 25, Tao Hanxin had a fever again. Over the next few days, his temperature peaked at 39.4 C. The family couldn't believe it and got a new thermometer. "I was worried it might be this, " Ms. Ma said.

In Tao's second CT scan of his lungs, two pebbly white areas became larger and larger, until black was barely visible. "The bigger the white area, the worse the lung function, " said Peng Zhiyong, director of the Department of Critical Care Medicine at central South Hospital. The doctor of the Tongji Hospital that receives a clinic tells Ma Meilian, double lung viral pneumonia, condition is serious, "want to use all concern to be hospitalized. "

On January 28, because there was no registration in Tongji Hospital, Ma Meilian had to take her husband to the nearby Wuhan Puai Hospital Fever Clinic. "I've never seen so many people in a hospital. People in line can walk around the block. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At about 20:00 on January 29, the hospital's fever clinic hall was filled with patients receiving fluids.

The doctor let Tao Hanxin in the consulting room observation, but the nurse told Ma Meilian, even consulting room is full. Impatient, she broke into the exam room. "We're just staying here, in case something happens, you can spare some oxygen for him, " Ms. Ma argued with the nurse.

Ms. Ma said her husband had multiple episodes of difficulty breathing and even convulsions. On the night of January 29, she took her husband back to Tongji Hospital for treatment at the fever clinic, where drips were hanging outside the lobby, either sitting on the steps or in the car.

To get oxygen, they bring their own folding beds to crash in the outpatient hallway.

That night, Tongji Hospital Security introduced the 35th Oxygen Tank. New tanks were brought in one after another for use by patients crammed into chairs for infusions. 20 meters long aisle, there are seven or eight fold-up bed. "people waiting for beds. "

On the same day, reporters visited a number of designated hospitals in Wuhan, found that almost every hospital fever clinics are long lines, people holding CT wearing masks, anxiously waiting.

Wuhan Ninth Hospital Fever Clinic Hall Guide Office Staff told reporters, "beds have long been full" ; designated hospitals in Wuhan City, the Seventh Hospital also posted in front of the "beds have been full" notice; Peng Zhiyong, director of the intensive-care unit at Wuhan University's Zhongnan Hospital, also told the reporter, "all just transferred one, and immediately came in one. ".

"More than 20 doctors and nurses meet 60,000 community residents. "

According to circular No. 7, the city's communities are responsible for the comprehensive screening of fever patients in the service areas, and sent to the Community Medical Center for screening and classification of the disease. For patients who need to go to the fever clinic, the districts will arrange to send vehicles to the designated fever clinic for treatment.

Ma Meilian Home Street secretary told reporters that according to the grading process, he had to the new Tao Han feedback to the community hospital, by them contact beds, responsible for referral. "The hospital beds are really tight, and I have been helping them to apply every day. It's been five or six days now, and still nothing, " the secretary said. The staff at the mayor's hotline told her that they would report back to Qiaokou District, with a 24-hour response.

But she never got the call.

Her Community Qiao Estuary Hanjiang Bridge Street Health Service Center, only more than 20 medical staff, but to meet 60,000 community residents. You can't even get a blood test in here. You can only take your temperature and prescribe medicine. Staff said the medical staff responsible for blood tests could not arrive at their posts. "One had a fever and was quarantined at home. The other returned home before the Spring Festival and can not return now. "

The resident, who claimed to have a temperature of 37.5 C, came for consultation. The doctor on duty advised him to "take some antiviral drugs and antibiotics, go home and continue to observe, and if there is a persistent fever, then report to the Community Hospital. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At noon on January 30, people with fever waited in a long line for treatment at Wuhan No. 6 Hospital.

The reporter visits discovery, a lot of community hospital that undertakes grading diagnose and treat first-screening job is faced with cure predicament.

On January 29, the community health center on Ganghua Street in Qingshan district, where Lin's family lives, was empty, with only two patients consulted. A staff member told the reporter, "here can only give you a finger, a blood test, do a preliminary screening of blood routine. No injection and no transfusion, I suggest you still go to the ninth hospital, where they can check everything. " This means that, even suspected cases, but also need to find their own way to designated hospitals, because there is "no referral vehicle. ".

In contrast, Jiufeng Street Community Health Service Center appears busy. On the afternoon of January 30, a police car was standing by at the entrance of the hospital, and two staff members were registering the temperature of each patient. To avoid cross-infection, they require only people with fever to enter the house.

The reporter saw on the registration form that more than 30 residents had been here in one morning. According to the staff, the function of the Community Hospital is to screen patients. If the patient's blood and body temperature are both at risk of new coronary pneumonia, they will arrange for transport to the nearest designated hospital, "We are better than other community hospitals. The Health Commission has given us a referral vehicle. Other community hospitals may not have one. " This referral vehicle, we've had about a dozen deliveries this morning, all suspected cases.

According to a community hospital staff member who did not want to be named, the grading of care has taken some of the pressure off, but there are still many suspected cases, leading to the shortage of beds and overcrowding in designated hospitals.

Community Hospital: material shortage and work pressure

In addition to the problem of case transfer, many community workstations have also experienced a shortage of protective materials and overwork of staff.

Qin Ying, a community secretary in Hongshan District, has been in contact with a fever patient in one of her precincts. "He had a fever for more than 10 days. It was listed as a viral pneumonia. When he arrived, he asked us to send a car to take him to the hospital, but he was later diagnosed with a new viral pneumonia. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On January 30, Ms. Ma's community hospital was unable to get to work and was forced to provide temperature readings and prescriptions.

She and her co-workers only have face masks. "We don't know if there are potential new cases of CAP coming in every day, but we can only reduce the number of times we go home. " She has asked her son and his family to move elsewhere. "He's only four years old. We don't want to infect them. ".

Qin Ying hasn't had a rest for more than 20 days. Sometimes in the wee hours of the morning, taking calls from residents. "We are all on 24 hours a day, ready to respond to calls for help from the precinct. ".

Her return visit was eight pages long, with the fever patient's request written in black and the patient's condition written in red. Each entry is marked with the patient's name, Home Address, ID number, and time of return visit. So far, she has followed 21 patients.

According to circular No. 8 of January 24, the city is urgently calling for 6,000 patrol and online hire taxis, which will be distributed to 1,159 communities in the central urban area as emergency vehicles and will be used by the unified dispatch of the neighborhood committees of the communities, for community residents to provide door-to-door delivery of food, medicine, food delivery services; in principle, patients with fever can only be transported by professional means of transport of health and epidemic prevention departments, and in case of emergency, transportation by emergency vehicles is really needed, the community shall immediately report to the district health and epidemic prevention department for the driver to take the necessary isolation protective measures.

To Qin Ying's distress, individual residents do not understand why the community has a car, but can not send fever patients to the hospital. "We also want to ensure the safety of our volunteers. Like us, they only have normal medical masks, and they don't have protective clothing or goggles. But there is no way. The materials have to be given priority to the first-line medical staff, and we understand that. "

Some residents have complained about community inaction. Qin Ying said with a wry smile. For patients with fever travel, they can only first contact with the command, and then with the hospital, through a special channel to transport fever patients.

On January 29, Lin Mei's health institute in Qingshan district, one of Wuhan's newly announced third designated hospitals, was able to connect her to a bed at Wuhan's No. 2 Hospital. On January 31, Ms. Ma told reporters that they had been offered a spot in the hospital for nucleic acid testing.

"with a confirmed diagnosis, there is hope for beds. "

(under the pseudonym Lin Mei, Li Qing, Chen Feng, Chen Qiang and Qin Ying, you Tian Yi, a reporter with the Beijing News, contributed to this article.)
